<taxonomicName id="4C344D763C0B8A353F4A5444FDC7FE60" authority="de L. Nascimento &amp; Perger, 2018" authorityName="de L. Nascimento &amp; Perger" authorityYear="2018" box="[369,629,1572,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudolepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplarinus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B940EAE73C0B8A353F4A5444FDC7FE60" box="[369,629,1572,1595]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467">Pseudolepturges triplarinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A273579C3C0B8A353C455444FD7FFE60" box="[638,717,1572,1595]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and its potential ant model 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D763C0B8A353DC85444FEEBFE03" authority="Weddell" authorityName="Weddell" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplarinus">
<emphasis id="B940EAE73C0B8A353DC85444FEB2FE03" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467">Pseudomyrmex triplarinus</emphasis>
Weddell
</taxonomicName>
: (a) Trees of 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D763C0B8A353FE35421FD3DFE03" box="[472,655,1601,1624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Triplaris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="B940EAE73C0B8A353FE35421FD3DFE03" box="[472,655,1601,1624]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467">Triplaris americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Pav. Ex Meisn. (indicated by white arrows). (b) Ants of 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D763C0B8A353ED4543FFE5BFE2D" box="[239,489,1631,1654]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triplarinus">
<emphasis id="B940EAE73C0B8A353ED4543FFE5BFE2D" box="[239,489,1631,1654]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467">Pseudomyrmex triplarinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the stem of 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D763C0B8A353CAB543FFCBDFE2D" box="[656,783,1631,1654]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Triplaris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="americana">T. americana</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B8B36F53C088A363E9B535BFDF7F9C2" blockId="6.[160,1156,315,409]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1468">
<emphasis id="B940EAE73C088A363E9B535BFEAAF90F" bold="true" box="[160,280,315,340]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1468">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Abdomen with abundant pubescence, not obscuring integument; abdominal ventrite I about 1.5 the II length; II–IV slightly decreasing in length; 
<collectionCode id="ED25AE303C088A363DDC533EFC44F92D" box="[999,1014,350,374]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="6" pageNumber="1468" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
trapezoidal, apex with short, thick blackish setae.
</paragraph>
